00:02:57:160000.Dialogue: Are you saying that you've been holding back?

00:03:04:190000.Speaker: Howard

00:03:12:050000.Dialogue: Well, I've dated plenty of women. There was Joyce Kim... Leslie Winkle...

00:03:20:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:20:090000.Dialogue: Notify the editors of the Oxford English Dictionary. The word plenty has been redefined to mean two.

00:03:27:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:27:230000.Dialogue: What about that girl last year at Comic-Con?

00:03:32:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:32:010000.Dialogue: What happens in costume at Comic-Con stays at Comic-Con.

00:03:36:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:36:030000.Dialogue: You're saying that because of what happened to you.

00:03:41:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:41:160000.Dialogue: It wasn't your fault. He was dressed as a green Orion slave girl.

00:03:47:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:47:030000.Dialogue: How did we get on me?! We were mocking Leonard for not moving on. Dude, you have totally not moved on.

00:03:53:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:53:010000.Dialogue: Yes, I have. It's just a matter of actually making a date with someone.

00:03:58:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:58:140000.Dialogue: Well... there's Joyce Kim. But she defected back to North Korea, so...

00:04:24:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:24:090000.Dialogue: You'd hit particulate soil in a colloidal suspension.

00:04:32:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:32:080000.Dialogue: I like Leslie, but she's not interested in dating as much as using men as tools for stress release.

00:04:41:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:41:160000.Dialogue: Go get yourself a little rebound stress release.

00:04:44:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:44:150000.Dialogue: Technically, it would only be rebound if he and Penny had actually engaged in physical intimacy.

00:04:49:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:49:000000.Dialogue: Like you and Richard the slave girl?

00:04:53:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:53:040000.Dialogue: I bought him dinner and we kissed once! That was it. And he told me his name was Kimberly.

00:05:04:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:04:090000.Dialogue: You know how I know we're not in the matrix?

00:05:13:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:13:040000.Dialogue: If we were, the food would be better.

00:05:21:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:21:220000.Dialogue: Hello, to you... insufficiently intelligent person.

00:05:26:150000.Speaker: Leslie
00:05:26:150000.Dialogue: Ooh, rush me to the burn unit.

00:05:31:210000.Speaker: Leslie
00:05:31:210000.Dialogue: Do you have a second? I need to ask you something.

00:06:01:180000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:01:180000.Dialogue: So, I heard your relationship with Penny crashed to the ground like blue ice falling out of an airplane lavatory.

00:06:09:230000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:09:230000.Dialogue: Actually, I read it. Wolowitz texted me.

00:06:13:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:13:170000.Dialogue: Like blue ice falling out of an airplane lavatory, yeah.

00:06:17:090000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:17:090000.Dialogue: I thought it was a pretty good one. I gave him an LOL.

00:06:21:070000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:21:070000.Dialogue: Anyway, it got me thinking. Now that you're unattached, maybe we can revisit our previous attachment.

00:06:27:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:27:020000.Dialogue: Are you suggesting another bout of stress release?

00:06:30:050000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:30:050000.Dialogue: No, I'm all done with casual sex. From now on, I'm fully committed to the traditional relationship paradigm.

00:06:44:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:44:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, I can see how that would-- a bunch of people?

00:06:48:060000.Speaker: Leslie
00:06:48:060000.Dialogue: Anyway, I figure it's time to slow things down and, who better to slow things down with than you?

00:06:57:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:57:230000.Dialogue: So, how do you suggest we proceed?

00:07:00:190000.Speaker: Leslie
00:07:00:190000.Dialogue: Your place, we'll order Chinese, you'll rent a movie-- artsy, but accessible-- then light petting, no coitus.

00:07:10:010000.Speaker: Leslie
00:07:10:010000.Dialogue: I'll leave the details up to you. It's better if you assume the male role.

00:08:11:040000.Dialogue: - All right, all right. Nevertheless, I have one now and I'd appreciate it if you would, make yourself scarce.

00:10:47:090000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. That was a little abrupt.

00:11:03:020000.Dialogue: Sorry to interrupt. Battery's dying. Continue.

00:11:08:090000.Speaker: Leslie
00:11:08:090000.Dialogue: Genetic weakness, right. There's the lactose intolerance.

00:11:15:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:15:030000.Dialogue: When his uncles sit around the dinner table, they look like a half carton of eggs.

00:11:39:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:39:050000.Dialogue: Okay, my uncles are bald, but my Aunt Edna is one of the hairiest women you'll ever meet.

00:11:45:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:45:090000.Dialogue: Sweet lady. Always tickles when she hugs me.

00:12:02:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:02:130000.Dialogue: I'm sorry about all of Sheldon's interruptions. He can be a bit of an eccentric.

00:12:06:220000.Speaker: Leslie
00:12:06:220000.Dialogue: If by eccentric you mean passive-aggressive East Texas blowhole, I agree.

00:12:13:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:13:020000.Dialogue: I think tonight was a very good start.

00:12:14:230000.Speaker: Leslie
00:12:14:230000.Dialogue: Me, too. You sure you're okay postponing intercourse until our relationship is past the initial viability test?

00:12:22:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:22:030000.Dialogue: No problem, I'm very skilled at postponing intercourse.

00:12:26:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:26:230000.Dialogue: I guess I'll call you and we'll arrange another evening.

00:12:30:030000.Speaker: Leslie
00:12:30:030000.Dialogue: I believe protocol dictates you wait a minimum of 18 hours before you call so I'm not repulsed by your cloying eagerness.

00:12:37:080000.Speaker: Leslie
00:12:37:080000.Dialogue: Again, it's your decision. You're the man.

00:12:39:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:39:230000.Dialogue: It wasn't my cat. It was an experiment designed by this guy named Schroedinger.

00:12:50:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:50:050000.Dialogue: No, he was some kind of scientist. Let me start again. - Hey, Leonard.

00:13:10:120000.Speaker: Leslie
00:13:10:120000.Dialogue: That ain't gonna make your point.

00:13:41:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:41:200000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, I am not going back to the Renaissance fair.

00:13:45:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:45:170000.Dialogue: Come on, there's so few places I can wear my jester costume.

00:13:51:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:51:150000.Dialogue: I don't care. There are far too many historical anomalies for my comfort.

00:13:55:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:55:180000.Dialogue: Okay, how about this? You can go dressed as a Star Trek science officer exploring a planet similar to Earth in the 1500s.

00:14:17:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:17:130000.Dialogue: Why don't we all move over there so Leslie can join us?

00:14:26:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:26:220000.Dialogue: If you're having trouble deciding where to sit, may I suggest one potato, two potato? Or as I call it, the Leslie Winkle experimental methodology.

00:14:58:160000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.

00:14:58:160000.Dialogue: Third floor tonight... mixing it up?

00:15:05:080000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:05:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:05:080000.Dialogue: I still don't understand why you don't go to dinner or something.

00:15:08:100000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:08:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:08:100000.Dialogue: All right, let's say I go to dinner alone, and during the meal, I have to use the restroom. How do I know someone's not touching my food?

00:15:19:230000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:19:230000.Speaker: Penny

00:15:22:020000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:22:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:22:020000.Dialogue: Penny, hold on. Are you sure things can't work out with you and Leonard?

00:15:27:050000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:27:050000.Speaker: Penny

00:15:28:090000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:28:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:28:090000.Dialogue: I'm just wondering if you really gave it the old college try.

00:15:33:180000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:33:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:33:180000.Dialogue: Or in your case, the old community college try.

00:15:38:080000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:38:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:38:080000.Dialogue: Okay, where is this coming from?

00:15:41:060000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:41:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:41:060000.Dialogue: Leonard is upstairs right now with my archenemy.

00:15:44:180000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:44:180000.Speaker: Penny

00:15:46:120000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:46:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:46:120000.Dialogue: The Dr. Doom to my Mr. Fantastic. The Dr. Octopus to my Spider-Man, the Dr. Sivana to my Captain Marvel.

00:15:53:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:53:030000.Speaker: Penny

00:15:55:010000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:55:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:55:010000.Dialogue: It's amazing how many supervillains have advanced degrees.

00:15:59:160000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:15:59:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:59:160000.Dialogue: Graduate school should do a better job of screening those people out.

00:16:03:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:03:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:03:030000.Dialogue: Sheldon, come back. You're losing me.

00:16:05:040000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:05:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:05:040000.Dialogue: It's Leslie Winkle, Penny. She belittles my research.

00:16:09:130000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:09:130000.Speaker: Penny

00:16:11:060000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:11:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:16:14:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:14:030000.Speaker: Penny

00:16:15:210000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:15:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:15:210000.Dialogue: Given this situation, I have no choice but to withdraw my previous objections to your ill-considered relationship with Leonard.

00:16:24:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:24:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:24:030000.Dialogue: Gee, well, thank you for that. But I think for now, Leonard and I are just gonna stay friends.

00:16:30:020000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:30:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:30:020000.Dialogue: No, that response is unacceptable to me.

00:16:34:110000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:34:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:34:110000.Dialogue: Sheldon, you are a smart guy...

00:16:36:090000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:36:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:36:090000.Dialogue: I'm smart? I'd have to lose 60 IQ points to be classified as smart.

00:16:42:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:42:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:42:030000.Dialogue: - Are you gonna let me talk?

00:16:45:040000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:45:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:45:040000.Dialogue: You must know that if Leonard and Leslie want to be together, nothing you can do is gonna stop it.

00:16:50:110000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:50:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:50:110000.Dialogue: You continue to underestimate my capabilities, madam.

00:16:55:050000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:16:55:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:55:050000.Dialogue: Let me put it this way. If you're really Leonard's friend, you will support him no matter who he wants to be with.

00:17:01:070000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:01:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:01:070000.Dialogue: Wait a minute. Why am I doing all the giving here?

00:17:05:070000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:05:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:05:070000.Dialogue: If Leonard's really my friend, why doesn't he have to support me and my hatred of Leslie Winkle?

00:17:12:040000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:12:040000.Speaker: Penny

00:17:15:160000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:15:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:15:160000.Dialogue: Now you're just making stuff up.

00:17:18:170000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:18:170000.Speaker: Penny

00:17:22:220000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:22:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:22:220000.Dialogue: Mario... If only I could control everyone the way I control you.

00:17:30:030000.Scene: The stairs. Sheldon is playing on his computer at the end of the long extension cord.
00:17:30:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:30:030000.Dialogue: Hop, you little plumber, hop, hop, hop.

00:17:37:150000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:17:37:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:37:150000.Dialogue: When the two of you reach a natural stopping point,

00:17:39:210000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:17:39:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:39:210000.Dialogue: I'd like to have a word.

00:17:42:060000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:17:42:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:42:060000.Dialogue: If the word is pee-pee, just do it.

00:17:50:060000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:17:50:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:50:060000.Dialogue: Leonard, you're my friend, and friends support their friends... apparently. So I'm withdrawing my objection to your desire to have a relationship with Leslie.

00:18:01:080000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:01:080000.Speaker: Leonard

00:18:14:030000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:14:030000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:16:090000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:16:090000.Speaker: Leslie
00:18:16:090000.Dialogue: Hang on a second. Loop quantum gravity clearly offers more testable predictions than string theory.

00:18:22:100000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:22:100000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:25:180000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:25:180000.Speaker: Leslie
00:18:25:180000.Dialogue: For one thing, we expect quantized space-time to manifest itself as minute differences in the speed of light for different colors.

00:18:32:070000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:32:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:32:070000.Dialogue: Balderdash. Matter clearly consists of tiny strings.

00:18:37:190000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:37:190000.Speaker: Leslie
00:18:37:190000.Dialogue: Are you gonna let him talk to me like that?

00:18:45:010000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:45:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:45:010000.Dialogue: Okay, well, there is a lot of merit to both theories.

00:18:47:160000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:47:160000.Speaker: Leslie
00:18:47:160000.Dialogue: No, there isn't. Only loop quantum gravity calculates the entropy of black holes.

00:18:54:230000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:54:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:54:230000.Dialogue: Sheldon, don't make that noise. It's disrespectful.

00:18:58:000000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:18:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:58:000000.Dialogue: I should hope so. It was a snort of derision.

00:19:01:150000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:01:150000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:01:150000.Dialogue: You agree with me, right? Loop quantum gravity is the future of physics.

00:19:06:050000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:06:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:06:050000.Dialogue: Sorry, Leslie, I guess I prefer my space stringy, not loopy.

00:19:11:010000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:11:010000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:11:010000.Dialogue: I'm glad I found out the truth about you before this went any further.

00:19:14:190000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:14:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:14:190000.Dialogue: Truth? What truth? We're talking about untested hypothes. It's no big deal.

00:19:19:120000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:19:120000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:19:120000.Dialogue: It isn't? Really? Tell me, how will we raise the children?

00:19:26:110000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:26:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:26:110000.Dialogue: I guess we wait until they're old enough and let them choose their own theory.

00:19:30:200000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:30:200000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:30:200000.Dialogue: We can't let them choose. They're children!

00:19:35:040000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:35:040000.Speaker: Leonard

00:19:38:060000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:38:060000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:38:060000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. I could have accepted our kids being genetically unable to eat ice cream or ever get a good view of a parade.

00:19:46:160000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:19:46:160000.Speaker: Leslie
00:19:46:160000.Dialogue: But this? This is a deal breaker.

00:20:01:180000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:20:01:180000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:20:06:010000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:20:06:010000.Speaker: Leonard

00:20:07:140000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard and Leslie are kissing.
00:20:07:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:07:140000.Dialogue: Only nine more months to Comic-con.

00:20:23:210000.Scene: The Renaissance Fair. The guys are in costume. Sheldon is Spock and has a tri-corder.
00:20:23:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:23:210000.Dialogue: Captain, I'm getting an unusual reading.

00:20:28:020000.Scene: The Renaissance Fair. The guys are in costume. Sheldon is Spock and has a tri-corder.
00:20:28:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:28:020000.Dialogue: That's great. You guys want corn dogs?

00:20:31:160000.Scene: The Renaissance Fair. The guys are in costume. Sheldon is Spock and has a tri-corder.
00:20:31:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:31:160000.Dialogue: That's a temporal anomaly. Corn dog's didn't come into existence till the first half of the 20th century.
